rComments: i'm really, really, sorry. to be done and unable to take another course w prof. boland.
Nice professor, knows her stuff. I learned nothing from this class and the amount of readings is ridiculous. If you don't do all the readings (even if you show up to every class) you won't do well.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: I have taken three classes with Boland and there is a reason I keep coming back for more! Boland is a great lecturer; her lectures are interesting and inspirational. Additionally, Boland reserves the first rows of her classroom as a designated screen free zone for students who wish to write pen to paper without the distraction of electronics.

I understand she is very supportive and sincere to her students. However, as a student with English as a second language, her class was full of theory and unclear concepts. The course itself was very conceptual and she grades very harsh on writing which can be tricky for many international students.

This class tends to get boring and you had to go to every lecture if you wanted to do somewhat well. Way too many essays, and then ended up marking extremely had on all of them. I don't recommend taking this class unless you're aiming to get a 60-65. Also doesn't give proper reviews for midterms/finals which results in having to study everything
Wonderful Prof! One of my favorite at UofT! Super super caring and passionate about her course.

Amazing professor, grading was fair and really teaches a lot. You get out of this course what you put in, and you will get your moneys worth (tuition), with the amount of content you will learn about in this course. Amazing lectures with videos, and an even better professor. Due to the fact that she is liked, prepare to line up for office hours
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Professor Boland is by far the best prof I've had at U of T. Both the way she designs her assignments and the feedback she gives on them has greatly helped to improve my skills in writing and researching. I frequently refer back to her comments while completing other assignments. I always left class feeling enthused about the topics she discussed.
One of the best I met in UofT. Considerate and gives good grades. Assignments are interesting.

Great professor. I'm not in geography, but this course was well worth it. Very helpful  prof, useful tutorials and very clear readings (there were some strange ones this year- but the prof has confirmed she's removing them for 2016!)

A great class. Alana is very passionate about China, and has done a lot of research over the years on the ground and has the experiences to share.  The class is a little long (3 hours) & It may seem a little overwhelming on day one knowing there is a quiz week 3, a midterm and 2 (short) essay assignments but easy to manage. I recommend this class!

She is a great prof, very helpful. the course can get boring, but it is very easy! its a bird course if you need one. she is very passionate about her class which makes it better, she is a great prof!

Alana is very nice, and is really excited about teaching. The mid-term for this class was really hard, however the assignments and tutorials were pretty good, fairly simple. The final exam was easier than the midterm and was good for drawing concepts of the course together.

Best Prof I have had yet.  Really goes the extra miles for her students.  Love her!!  Many students in the class are of Chinese background and/or have a high passion for China studies.  The lectures do appeal to everybody, however.  Workload is very high, and the marking is quite tough.  But you will definitely learn a lot.

I really enjoyed her teaching, the subject material, and the conversations we shared. Unfortunately, I found her assignments uninteresting (mostly literature reviews; no opportunity for research) and the examination was surprisingly difficult in relation to the course. Overall a positive experience.

hardest social science class ever - tonnes of painfully blase, repetitive readings.  be prepared to get to know a lot of wishy-washy isms in a wishy-washy way.  very hard marker, but makes up for this by being very helpful.  Alana (Al-ain-a) is willing to go the extra mile for her students, and is very easy to talk to.  takes a novel approach

One of the best professors I have had. She is extremely passionate about the material and open to tangential discussions that end up enriching the approach to the material as well. She is there to learn as much as she is there to teach. Very valuable learning experience. The workload is extremely heavy though, be aware.
great prof, passionate about course material. helpful and cares about students... assignments are pretty tough tho
y
I love her randomness. Made stats relatively painless and entertaining as it possibly can be. Lets put it this way...im looking for other classes she teaches to take. Exccelent prof!
Boland rocks.  I hate stats, but she is really engaging and has a great sense of humour.  Shes also incredible helpful when you ask her for help!  Amazing Prof
Amazing! Obviously very passionate about the material - only reason I took the course was b/c she was teaching it!
Amazing prof. She made stats a lot less painful. She's funny, engaging and genuinely shows concern for her students. If you need a stats credit, take the course with her!

Excellent professor! she makes boring stats so interesting! humourous and helpful! fair tests, very enjoyable course! probably the best stats prof out there! HIGHLY RECOMMENDED! best of all, easy to pick up marks from assignments! :P
Amazing prof - floored me and inspired me in a statistics class - is that possible?  Would DEFINITLY recommend her
Interesting prof, very knowledgeable about China.  Great lectures, hard assignments though.  Good sense of humour.  I'd recommend taking her class
What suprise, a prof. at U of T with a sense of humor. She makes sadistics relatively fun.
Very nice.
the best prof. i ever hv..
OM*G I GOT A 60% WOOHOO!! thanks again prof boland =D
super helpful. takes time to talk, get to know you and help you anyway she can. takes interest in student's. knowledgeable and makes you want to learn mroe about china.

I HATE math but needed any stats course for my program, and I'm glad I took this one!  She's very helpful in and outside class, and her lectures are easy to follow.  Don't know if I'll pass the course, but that's because of me and not her.
learn a lot from her!! Great prof!
Harder course; Boland is very very helpful; interesting; learned alot
made me not want to kill myself in math class
Fantastic Professor...you actually learn from her !
Really makes boring stuff as interesting as possible - a great prof.
